Squirt is a New Zealand children's television show, produced in Dunedin.
It had been aired since 1996 and on two different TV networks, coming to a close on the 25 November, 2006.
It was notable for Dunedin based production company TaylorMade, and Animation Research Limited's (ARL) pioneering use of "live" motion capture, used in the 3D animation of the digital co-host Spike The Penguin.
